      "note": "No persisted-preference staging is required. Start page is the CRM customer list (crm-customers.html); step 1 opens Customer 360 by a genuine row click. The lesson pins the SAME live member both times it opens Customer 360 (step 1 and the step-9 return) via the deterministic custActiveRow resolver (first active row with a real plan = CUST-4420000001643501 'visa cardholder', Cleanest Ultra Unlimited, CLE17), so Membership and Notes read the same account. Cross-module navigation is by genuine in-app clicks only (the engine navigates solely to startUrl): rail Settings -> settings.html, the Users & Security and Operations sidebar GROUP headers are expanded with unless-guards (opened only if the target link is not already visible, since group state is shared across the profile and was observed both collapsed and expanded on load), the Security Level / Refund Reasons sidebar LINKS, and rail CRM back to the list. Every settings sub-page self-expands its sidebar on load (probe-verified July 12: settingsReady + sidebarExpanded true). LIVE-vs-CORPUS DRIFT (residuals, shown as truth, see report): the July 9 corpus behind the narration had 'Failed to fetch' list bodies and dash KPIs on both settings pages and parked the Customer 360 values; on July 12 all three surfaces render live and loaded, so the video shows the real data and the callouts caption the drift."
    }
